I doubt it. It is usually taught by visiting professors, so it isn't offered regularly. Furthermore, the first few units of the class (i.e. automata theory and computability) are losing relevance as modern research topics in theoretical computer science. I think every now and then, CS 278 is offered, so you might want to look into that.
